WEBVTT

00:04.371 --> 00:05.638
♪ ♪

00:05.705 --> 00:08.108
Hey, hon, do we have
any more crackers?

00:08.174 --> 00:11.678
It's 4:00-- my morning sickness
is rude as hell.

00:11.745 --> 00:13.747
Sorry, I ate 'em all.

00:13.813 --> 00:16.549
I've been having a touch
of morning sickness myself.

00:16.616 --> 00:18.017
Really, hon?

00:18.084 --> 00:19.352
Because I'm the one

00:19.419 --> 00:21.421
who's been literally growing
a human being

00:21.488 --> 00:23.156
for the past seven weeks.

00:23.223 --> 00:26.159
But, you know,
by all means, eat up.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.361
You are such an as...

00:28.428 --> 00:32.432
Astonishingly
thoughtful husband?

00:33.433 --> 00:34.534
I'll give you that.

00:34.601 --> 00:36.302
Now give me the crackers.

00:37.404 --> 00:39.305
I also got you some applesauce
and ginger tea.

00:39.372 --> 00:41.341
I remember how sick you were
with Grover.

00:41.408 --> 00:43.343
You are so sweet.

00:43.410 --> 00:45.111
(chuckles)

00:46.246 --> 00:49.749
What's wrong?

00:46.246 --> 00:49.749
Well, I remember how sick
you were with Grover.

00:50.784 --> 00:53.052
So, how's your
family research going?

00:53.119 --> 00:57.056
Oh, my-- this Find Your Way
DNA website is amazing.

00:57.123 --> 01:00.160
It turns out there's
a whole world inside of my spit.

01:01.461 --> 01:03.563
But, you know, I have
a sixth cousin once removed

01:03.630 --> 01:04.764
who lives right here

01:04.831 --> 01:06.132
in California.

01:06.199 --> 01:07.634
His name is Terry B. Davis.

01:07.700 --> 01:09.002
Look at this guy.

01:09.068 --> 01:10.637
GEMMA:
Oh!

01:10.703 --> 01:14.140
He's African American!

01:14.207 --> 01:15.241
I know.

01:15.308 --> 01:16.476
Kind of, uh,

01:16.543 --> 01:18.611
explains my dance moves, huh?

01:22.715 --> 01:24.284
Calm down, Dave.

01:24.350 --> 01:26.386
Let's not bring our milkshakes
to the yard just yet.

01:27.387 --> 01:28.788
I got to go tell Calvin.

01:28.855 --> 01:31.658
I am Black and I am proud.

01:31.724 --> 01:35.195
And I'm gonna say it out loud.

01:36.296 --> 01:38.431
Please don't go over there
bugging Calvin.

01:38.498 --> 01:39.766
Gemma, Calvin's my best friend.

01:39.833 --> 01:41.668
How could I ever bug him?

01:43.269 --> 01:45.338
Why are you bugging me now,
Dave?

01:47.640 --> 01:48.575
Calvin...

01:48.641 --> 01:51.778
look at this handsome fella.

01:51.845 --> 01:53.813
That's my cousin Terry.

01:53.880 --> 01:56.716
If he says that he's
a Nigerian prince

01:56.783 --> 01:59.486
and needs a small investment
to free up his millions,

01:59.552 --> 02:01.287
don't do it.

02:03.456 --> 02:06.993
Wait a minute. You're related
to Terry B. Davis?

02:07.060 --> 02:09.596
Yeah. That "B"
stands for Butler.

02:12.332 --> 02:14.033
No.

02:14.100 --> 02:16.669
That "B" stands
for "blessed."

02:19.072 --> 02:20.440
Calvin, we're related.

02:20.507 --> 02:23.243
Say what, now?

02:23.309 --> 02:25.512
Whoa, whoa, hold...
Let-let me see that.

02:25.578 --> 02:27.480
Oh, wow, Dad, it's true.

02:27.547 --> 02:28.615
And if Terry

02:28.681 --> 02:30.717
is Dave's cousin...

02:30.783 --> 02:33.019
And he's also
your cousin...

02:33.086 --> 02:35.288
That means
you are...

02:35.355 --> 02:37.123
Hopefully adopted.

02:39.359 --> 02:40.693
Bring it in, cuz!

02:42.395 --> 02:44.464
♪ Welcome to the block,
welcome to the neighborhood ♪

02:44.531 --> 02:45.532
♪ Welcome to the hood. ♪

02:51.571 --> 02:52.572
Hey.

02:52.639 --> 02:55.708
I thought you were not
going over to bug Calvin.

02:55.775 --> 02:59.546
Ha. We are family--
I'm allowed to bug.

02:59.612 --> 03:01.247
What?

03:01.314 --> 03:04.117
Yeah, we just figured out
we're related.

03:04.183 --> 03:05.251
Oh, no.

03:05.318 --> 03:07.220
We ain't figured
out nothing yet.

03:08.388 --> 03:12.025
Oh, Tina, you've always felt
like family to me.

03:12.091 --> 03:13.226
Aw. Same here, Gemma.

03:13.293 --> 03:15.295
You're my sister
from another mister.

03:15.361 --> 03:18.064
Aw, you're my siz
from another wiz.

03:18.131 --> 03:20.033
That sounds nasty.

03:20.099 --> 03:22.235
Sorry, that sounded
way less gross in my head.

03:22.302 --> 03:23.770
(laughs)

03:23.836 --> 03:27.507
You know, this ancestry stuff,
this isn't science.

03:27.574 --> 03:29.008
It's voodoo.

03:29.075 --> 03:30.577
It's about as legit

03:30.643 --> 03:33.513
as getting your fortune
out of a cookie.

03:33.580 --> 03:36.115
Well, Pop,
my fortune cookie told me

03:36.182 --> 03:38.785
my future was gonna be
a whole lot brighter.

03:38.851 --> 03:42.188
Maybe it meant whiter.
(laughing)

03:42.255 --> 03:44.724
Welcome to the family,
Cousin Dave.

03:46.359 --> 03:49.729
Dad, actually, these websites
are usually based on DNA,

03:49.796 --> 03:52.231
and there's nothing
more science-ier than DNA.

03:52.298 --> 03:53.533
"More science-ier"?

03:53.600 --> 03:54.500
Mm-hmm.

03:54.567 --> 03:55.602
Go get your diploma.

03:55.668 --> 03:57.570
They owe me a refund.

03:58.838 --> 04:00.673
No, no.
If you look real close,

04:00.740 --> 04:04.177
you can see that Dave and Pop
kind of favor each other.

04:04.644 --> 04:06.980
Look at Pop.
He got two eyes.

04:07.046 --> 04:10.183
Now look at Dave.
He got two eyes, too!

04:11.751 --> 04:13.119
No, you know what?

04:13.186 --> 04:14.454
No, I'm gonna get to
the bottom of this.

04:14.520 --> 04:16.089
I don't need DNA.

04:16.155 --> 04:20.259
I have a Aunt Desiray, who knows
all the family secrets.

04:20.326 --> 04:23.229
Yeah, she may be old, but
that bourbon keeps her sharp.

04:23.296 --> 04:27.066
Remember when she told us
about Uncle Gus's secret family

04:27.133 --> 04:29.202
that he was hiding
from his side family,

04:29.268 --> 04:31.704
and then the real family
found out at the funeral.

04:31.771 --> 04:34.474
Caused another funeral.

04:34.540 --> 04:36.075
♪ ♪

04:36.142 --> 04:41.180
Hey, why aren't you laying
down, eating bonbons,

04:41.247 --> 04:44.250
and watching Tamron Hall
like any sane pregnant woman?

04:45.118 --> 04:47.320
I wish.
I have to make cupcakes

04:47.387 --> 04:49.656
for Grover's Scout troop,
but-but every time

04:49.722 --> 04:51.658
I crack an egg I get nauseous,
and this recipe

04:51.724 --> 04:54.394
calls for 12 eggs.

04:51.724 --> 04:54.394
Mm.

04:54.460 --> 04:56.562
So that'd be a barfer's dozen?

04:56.629 --> 05:00.500
(laughing)

05:01.367 --> 05:03.603
All right, well, okay,
all right, well, let me help.

05:03.670 --> 05:05.271
You know,
I could whup up some cupcakes

05:05.338 --> 05:07.173
that'd make you want
to slap your mama.

05:07.240 --> 05:10.710
The only mamas I want to slap
are those judgy troop moms.

05:10.777 --> 05:12.512
Is it that serious?

05:12.578 --> 05:16.082
Yes. If I don't hit it out
of the park with these cupcakes,

05:16.149 --> 05:20.386
I'd never be able to show
my face at SoulCycle again.

05:20.453 --> 05:21.587
You poor thing.

05:21.654 --> 05:23.523
It ain't easy being white,
is it?

05:25.124 --> 05:27.026
You have no idea.

05:27.093 --> 05:29.629
♪ ♪

05:30.396 --> 05:32.331
So, Auntie, we
invited you here

05:32.398 --> 05:34.634
to get some family
information.

05:34.701 --> 05:37.070
We were wondering,

05:37.136 --> 05:39.739
are we related
to any Johnsons?

05:39.806 --> 05:41.607
Oh, boy, we Black.

05:41.674 --> 05:44.243
We're related to
a lot of Johnsons.

05:45.211 --> 05:48.247
Well, I meant
any white Johnsons.

05:48.314 --> 05:50.650
Come to think of it,

05:50.717 --> 05:53.753
back when our family was
in Tuscaloosa,

05:53.820 --> 05:57.690
a Black Butler-- who
happened to be a butler--

05:57.757 --> 06:01.594
had relations with
a white Johnson.

06:01.661 --> 06:03.963
Thankfully, he
skipped town,

06:04.030 --> 06:05.998
'cause when that
baby come out,

06:06.065 --> 06:07.133
no doubt

06:07.200 --> 06:09.535
there was some
Butler in him.

06:11.504 --> 06:13.272
That's not good.

06:14.607 --> 06:16.576
A-And that boy was

06:16.642 --> 06:20.580
your great-grandfather
Cofedelius.

06:20.646 --> 06:22.482
Wow, Pop.

06:22.548 --> 06:24.050
So the DNA was right.

06:24.117 --> 06:24.784
Damn.

06:24.851 --> 06:27.086
I am related to Dave.

06:27.153 --> 06:28.321
Ah, yes!

06:28.387 --> 06:30.189
Science wins again.

06:30.256 --> 06:32.091
♪ ♪

06:32.158 --> 06:33.726
TINA:
Welcome, new family members

06:33.793 --> 06:37.130
to our first official
family dinner.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.200
("We Are Family" playing)

06:41.267 --> 06:44.036
♪ We are family ♪

06:45.304 --> 06:48.207
♪ I got all my
brothers with me. ♪

06:50.777 --> 06:52.378
What do you think, Calvin?

06:52.445 --> 06:53.746
Throwing it back, old-school.

06:53.813 --> 06:55.681
Yeah, I'm thinking
about pulling an Uncle Gus

06:55.748 --> 06:57.750
and starting a new family.

06:59.652 --> 07:01.988
Calvin, how come
you have not responded

07:02.054 --> 07:04.190
to the family group chat
I started?

07:04.257 --> 07:05.491
Because I left that chat,

07:05.558 --> 07:07.627
just like I'm about to leave
this one.

07:07.693 --> 07:09.729
Can I take that for you?

07:09.796 --> 07:13.132
What? You don't think I'm
strong enough to hold a dish?

07:13.199 --> 07:16.269
Oh, I forgot
my pregnant woman policy:

07:16.335 --> 07:18.604
"Step away until Labor Day."

07:20.573 --> 07:21.541
Ooh, hey, guys.

07:21.607 --> 07:25.178
Hey, check this out.
I did more research online

07:25.244 --> 07:27.180
into our family history.

07:27.246 --> 07:29.482
Ah, yeah, we're listening,
Cousin Dave.

07:30.483 --> 07:31.684
It turns out

07:31.751 --> 07:35.388
both sides of our family own
several plots of land together.

07:35.454 --> 07:37.423
Oh, what? Really?
We were land barons?

07:37.490 --> 07:39.058
Yeah, yeah.
Look at that.

07:39.125 --> 07:40.726
In Tuscaloosa, Alabama.

07:40.793 --> 07:44.263
Hey, you know, uh, Aunt Desiray
was talking about Tuscaloosa.

07:44.330 --> 07:47.066
She said that
my great-grandfather

07:47.133 --> 07:49.435
Cofedelius had land there.

07:49.502 --> 07:50.670
Really? What happened to it?

07:50.736 --> 07:52.438
No one knows.

07:52.505 --> 07:55.107
All the family says is that
after he lost his land,

07:55.174 --> 07:57.276
he became an alcoholic.

07:57.343 --> 07:59.645
Uh, well, that's because
at the turn of the century,

07:59.712 --> 08:04.317
the banks made it impossible
for certain people to own land.

08:04.383 --> 08:06.252
Mm-hmm. You know
what that mean.

08:06.319 --> 08:07.687
Black people.

08:09.288 --> 08:12.158
(chuckles)
Uh, well, hold on.

08:12.225 --> 08:14.393
Not necessarily.

08:14.460 --> 08:15.695
No, yeah, he's right.

08:15.761 --> 08:17.730
It's Black people.

08:18.564 --> 08:20.566
Oh. And Native Americans

08:20.633 --> 08:22.034
and Chinese.

08:22.101 --> 08:23.636
I'm gonna stop scrolling.

08:25.304 --> 08:28.040
Yeah, these records show
that Dave's side of the family

08:28.107 --> 08:30.142
got the land from our side.

08:30.209 --> 08:31.477
How much did they pay for it?

08:31.544 --> 08:34.447
Ooh, uh, perhaps I should
substitute the word "got"

08:34.513 --> 08:36.115
with "stole."

08:37.750 --> 08:39.685
Wait-wait-wait-wait.
So you're telling me

08:39.752 --> 08:42.321
Dave's family stole
from your family?

08:42.388 --> 08:43.689
Yes, Gemma,

08:43.756 --> 08:46.392
that is exactly
what they're saying.

08:48.294 --> 08:50.730
So, you know that Weedwacker
you borrowed three weeks ago?

08:50.796 --> 08:54.333
I'm gonna need that back,
plus about $7 million.

08:54.400 --> 08:55.401
♪ ♪

09:02.241 --> 09:04.043
All right, fam, come eat.

09:04.110 --> 09:05.311
Hey!

09:04.110 --> 09:05.311
Hey, babe,

09:05.378 --> 09:07.346
you remember
how my Aunt Desiray

09:07.413 --> 09:11.217
was talking about my
great-grandfather Cofedelius?

09:11.284 --> 09:13.119
Oh, yeah, he was a mean drunk.

09:13.185 --> 09:16.989
Mm-hmm, you'd be mean, too,
if your name was Cofedelius.

09:17.790 --> 09:19.158
The point is,

09:19.225 --> 09:21.160
is that he didn't start drinking

09:21.227 --> 09:23.663
till after his land was stolen.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.264
Well, who stole it?

09:31.604 --> 09:34.540
It was
Dave's great-great-grandfather.

09:34.607 --> 09:36.976
Oh, Lord. We're gonna
need more than chicken

09:37.043 --> 09:38.311
to get us through
this dinner.

09:38.377 --> 09:39.545
Nothing for me.

09:39.612 --> 09:42.281
I'm just gonna eat
my purse crackers.

09:43.282 --> 09:45.017
Let us pray.

09:45.651 --> 09:48.387
Dear Lord, thank you
for bringing us together

09:48.454 --> 09:50.122
and blessing this food,

09:50.189 --> 09:54.160
and thank you for not
letting Dave steal it. Amen.

09:54.226 --> 09:56.362
Okay, all right, you know what?

09:56.429 --> 09:57.997
I deserve that.

09:58.064 --> 09:59.265
No, you don't, Dave.

09:59.332 --> 10:01.400
To be fair, you
didn't steal anything.

10:01.467 --> 10:02.501
Exactly.

10:02.568 --> 10:04.136
His family did.

10:04.203 --> 10:06.272
Dave just benefited
from the racist laws

10:06.339 --> 10:09.342
that gave his family land
that contributed

10:09.408 --> 10:11.677
to the generational wealth
that was then passed down

10:11.744 --> 10:14.113
to make his life
a whole lot easier.

10:16.248 --> 10:18.651
To be fair,
I don't think that I received

10:18.718 --> 10:20.653
any generational wealth.

10:20.720 --> 10:22.788
Uh, look, Dave,
when you turned 16,

10:22.855 --> 10:24.457
did you get a car?

10:24.523 --> 10:27.393
Yeah, but it was a beat-up
bucket with 100,000 miles on it.

10:27.460 --> 10:28.761
Well, guess what I got.

10:28.828 --> 10:30.796
Every other weekend off,

10:30.863 --> 10:33.232
because I had a job!

10:34.867 --> 10:37.470
Did-did I mention
the car had no AC?

10:37.536 --> 10:40.172
Kalamazoo summers were very hot.

10:40.773 --> 10:42.441
So were cotton fields.

10:42.508 --> 10:45.344
Damn it, Malcolm,
I was just about to say that.

10:46.245 --> 10:48.481
I guess everybody's
just gonna steal from me today.

10:48.547 --> 10:51.717
♪ ♪

10:52.685 --> 10:54.186
Oh, hey.

10:54.253 --> 10:55.621
Gemma.

10:54.253 --> 10:55.621
(gasps)
What's going on?

10:55.688 --> 10:58.357
Glad you're awake.
I had a rough night.

11:01.293 --> 11:03.195
What's wrong, Dave?

11:03.262 --> 11:05.664
I just hate knowing
that my family was a part

11:05.731 --> 11:08.100
of America's racist past.

11:08.167 --> 11:10.436
I am sure Calvin
doesn't really blame you

11:10.503 --> 11:13.539
for crimes that were committed
hundreds of years ago.

11:13.606 --> 11:14.540
Oh, really?

11:14.607 --> 11:17.009
Every time we leave their house,

11:17.076 --> 11:19.545
Calvin always says,
"Good night, Dave."

11:19.612 --> 11:21.547
Yesterday it was just...

11:21.614 --> 11:23.149
"Night."

11:25.551 --> 11:28.621
Trust me, Gemma, he is seething!

11:30.623 --> 11:32.625
Give him time to process it.

11:32.691 --> 11:35.361
Besides,
you can't change the past.

11:35.428 --> 11:38.030
We can only work to fix
the future.

11:38.097 --> 11:40.032
Raising Grover to be
an enlightened,

11:40.099 --> 11:43.235
anti-racist human is
a major part of that.

11:44.236 --> 11:46.405
And teaching him
to put the seat down.

11:47.239 --> 11:50.176
Or you could learn
to put the seat up. I mean...

11:50.242 --> 11:51.377
Sorry, what?

11:54.213 --> 11:58.250
If that's something that
you felt like you wanted to do.

12:00.419 --> 12:01.620
Do you smell that?

12:01.687 --> 12:03.322
(gasps)
My cupcakes!

12:04.757 --> 12:06.292
Okay, d-don't panic.

12:06.358 --> 12:07.593
They... they could still--

12:07.660 --> 12:09.295
aah!-- they could
still taste good.

12:09.361 --> 12:10.429
(groans)

12:09.361 --> 12:10.429
Okay.

12:10.496 --> 12:13.065
Oh! Okay, time to panic.

12:13.132 --> 12:15.434
Wha-What's wrong?

12:13.132 --> 12:15.434
(gasping)

12:15.501 --> 12:18.003
It's burning!

12:19.205 --> 12:21.574
(gasps)
Geez, I thought
this was margarine.

12:21.640 --> 12:24.009
(grunts)

12:21.640 --> 12:24.009
I may have put wasabi in them.

12:25.544 --> 12:27.279
You did. No "may."

12:27.346 --> 12:29.081
You definitely did.

12:29.715 --> 12:31.283
And wasabi's green, Gemma.

12:31.350 --> 12:34.220
What kind of old margarine
are you okay with using?!

12:34.286 --> 12:36.522
♪ ♪

12:36.589 --> 12:38.757
All right, bye, babe.

12:39.225 --> 12:42.161
What the hell, Dave?

12:42.228 --> 12:44.363
Look, I'm sorry,
I just...

12:44.430 --> 12:47.166
feel horrible about what
my family did to yours.

12:47.233 --> 12:48.534
Well, you should.

12:48.601 --> 12:50.369
Now I got to get to my shop.

12:50.436 --> 12:53.072
Unless your family
stole that, too.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.141
Look, I just...

12:55.207 --> 12:58.511
How could they have been
so mean and coldhearted?

12:58.577 --> 13:00.479
Well, it was the 1800s.

13:00.546 --> 13:02.581
White folks didn't have
to pretend to be nice

13:02.648 --> 13:04.383
to Black folks back then.

13:04.450 --> 13:06.552
Just... first...

13:06.619 --> 13:08.087
Okay, Dave, move,

13:08.154 --> 13:09.655
before I forget
you're one of the good ones.

13:09.722 --> 13:11.524
Just hear me out.

13:11.590 --> 13:16.128
Now, I know I can't make up for
hundreds of years of oppression,

13:16.195 --> 13:17.730
but please...
(sighs)

13:17.796 --> 13:21.333
consider these my attempt
at reparations.

13:22.168 --> 13:24.637
Dave, I appreciate your offer,

13:24.703 --> 13:27.173
but you can't make this right.

13:27.239 --> 13:29.208
So you don't want
these Dodger tickets?

13:30.209 --> 13:32.411
Second row,
behind home plate?

13:33.412 --> 13:34.713
Oh.

13:34.780 --> 13:37.783
Well, I don't want 'em, but...

13:37.850 --> 13:41.053
I'll accept them
on behalf of my ancestors.

13:41.120 --> 13:43.255
What's that,
Great-Granddaddy?

13:43.322 --> 13:46.358
We could also use
a parking pass?

13:47.593 --> 13:49.395
♪ ♪

13:51.263 --> 13:54.033
These aren't so bad.

13:54.099 --> 13:55.601
(clacking)

13:59.104 --> 14:01.740
What unholy nightmare is this?

14:01.807 --> 14:05.077
Cupcakes never had
a chance, Miss Tina.

14:05.144 --> 14:08.047
Had a good run, Mom.
Can't stay on top forever.

14:08.113 --> 14:10.216
Just ask A-Rod.

14:11.350 --> 14:12.651
(sighs)

14:12.718 --> 14:14.253
Grover's troop meets in an hour.

14:14.320 --> 14:16.288
I really thought
I could do it myself.

14:16.355 --> 14:19.325
Mm, well, it's too bad
no one offered to help you.

14:19.391 --> 14:21.160
Multiple times.

14:21.227 --> 14:23.229
I know, and I appreciate it.

14:23.295 --> 14:24.230
I just didn't want Grover

14:24.296 --> 14:26.332
to think that
I'd be there for him any less

14:26.398 --> 14:28.234
now that there's a new baby
on the way.

14:28.300 --> 14:30.569
Look, I get it,
but accepting help doesn't mean

14:30.636 --> 14:32.571
that you love him any less.

14:32.638 --> 14:34.573
I guess you're right.

14:34.640 --> 14:36.709
Okay, so I'm
officially asking.

14:36.775 --> 14:39.612
Can I please get some
of your Black girl magic?

14:39.678 --> 14:41.580
Oh, I thought you
would never ask.

14:41.647 --> 14:43.082
(laughs)

14:43.148 --> 14:44.617
Let's see what
we're working with.

14:43.148 --> 14:44.617
Okay.

14:44.683 --> 14:47.319
Nothing. Absolutely nothing.

14:47.386 --> 14:48.654
Uh...

14:49.822 --> 14:53.325
I still have baking chocolate,
flour, mayonnaise, and...

14:53.392 --> 14:54.593
some Pop-Tarts.

14:54.660 --> 14:56.462
That's it?

14:56.528 --> 15:00.499
Oh. And some edible
strawberry massage oil

15:00.566 --> 15:02.434
we got for our anniversary.

15:02.501 --> 15:04.103
Ooh.

15:04.169 --> 15:06.338
Strawberry massage oil.

15:04.169 --> 15:06.338
(laughs)

15:06.405 --> 15:10.509
This is like
Fifty Shades of Hell's Kitchen.

15:10.576 --> 15:13.212
♪ ♪

15:18.350 --> 15:20.686
♪ Ooh, yeah. ♪

15:38.671 --> 15:40.406
Four dozen cupcakes?

15:40.472 --> 15:42.374
Oh, you're a lifesaver!

15:42.441 --> 15:43.742
With five minutes
to spare.

15:43.809 --> 15:46.545
Black girl magic
delivered.

15:47.379 --> 15:51.317
Is it me, or do they
look like little butts?

15:52.151 --> 15:54.186
Does your little butt
want it or not?

15:54.253 --> 15:55.321
Yes, I do.

15:55.387 --> 15:57.056
Thank you, Miss Tina.

15:57.122 --> 16:00.025
They smell like
strawberries.

16:00.092 --> 16:02.328
Oh, well,
that is a chef's secret.

16:02.394 --> 16:05.097
Mm-hmm.

16:02.394 --> 16:05.097
And your parents' secret, too.

16:05.164 --> 16:06.732
♪ ♪

16:08.267 --> 16:09.735
Mama!

16:09.802 --> 16:12.471
Dave is power-washing
the driveway again.

16:12.538 --> 16:14.139
Tell him to stop.

16:14.206 --> 16:15.341
Yep, well, now
he's out there

16:15.407 --> 16:16.442
weeding your roses.

16:16.508 --> 16:19.378
Tell him after he's done.

16:20.379 --> 16:22.614
(knocking)

16:23.482 --> 16:24.550
(chuckles): Hey.

16:23.482 --> 16:24.550
MARTY: Oh, hey.

16:24.616 --> 16:25.751
Oh, how did it go?

16:25.818 --> 16:27.553
Did they like my cupcakes?

16:27.619 --> 16:29.321
Liked? They loved them!

16:29.388 --> 16:32.257
I got a cooking badge,
and I didn't even make them!

16:33.492 --> 16:34.760
Well, no surprise there.

16:34.827 --> 16:37.096
My mama knows how
to put her foot in it.

16:37.162 --> 16:39.565
Well, that Black
girl magic is real.

16:39.631 --> 16:41.433
I even confessed
they were yours,

16:41.500 --> 16:42.701
and nobody gave me the side-eye.

16:42.768 --> 16:44.303
The troop moms
loved them so much,

16:44.370 --> 16:46.271
they want to pay you
to bake some more.

16:46.338 --> 16:49.775
Oh, well, I do love baking,
but I just do it as a hobby.

16:49.842 --> 16:51.276
Cheryl's having a party
tomorrow,

16:51.343 --> 16:53.445
and she wants to pay you
60 bucks a dozen

16:53.512 --> 16:54.680
for five dozen.

16:54.747 --> 16:56.081
Wait a minute.

16:56.148 --> 16:57.583
(mumbles)

16:58.384 --> 17:00.953
That's halfway
to a Chanel brooch.

17:01.453 --> 17:04.623
Well, looks like my hobby
just turned into a side hustle.

17:04.690 --> 17:07.192
♪ ♪

17:12.631 --> 17:14.133
(grunts)

17:14.199 --> 17:16.101
Aah!

17:20.139 --> 17:21.540
Oof!

17:21.607 --> 17:23.275
Gemma!

17:24.576 --> 17:26.578
Somebody!

17:26.645 --> 17:28.247
Help!

17:34.653 --> 17:37.122
Aah!
(groans)

17:39.391 --> 17:41.593
(groans)

17:41.660 --> 17:44.430
Oh. Hey-hey, man.

17:44.496 --> 17:46.265
You okay?

17:46.331 --> 17:48.367
Yeah.

17:48.434 --> 17:50.169
Little hurt, but, uh...

17:50.235 --> 17:52.771
just paying for the sins
of my fathers, so...

17:54.106 --> 17:56.175
What were you
doing up there?

17:56.241 --> 17:57.743
I was cleaning your gutters.

17:57.810 --> 17:59.745
No judgment, but it was
high time somebody did.

17:59.812 --> 18:02.181
Look, okay, all right,
that's it, stop it.

18:02.247 --> 18:03.081
Please. All right,

18:03.148 --> 18:05.651
no more cleaning,
no more Dodgers tickets,

18:05.717 --> 18:07.953
and no more fruit smoothies.

18:08.020 --> 18:11.356
Calvin, I still need to fix
what my family did.

18:12.357 --> 18:13.525
Look...

18:13.592 --> 18:16.962
I'm not gonna lie.
It bothered me.

18:17.629 --> 18:20.466
But I talked to Tina
about it, and...

18:20.532 --> 18:23.569
I realized I shouldn't be
directing my anger at you.

18:24.570 --> 18:26.538
All right? This is
so much bigger than me and you.

18:26.605 --> 18:30.042
It's such a ugly reflection
on the history of our country.

18:30.108 --> 18:32.411
I mean, people degraded
each other

18:32.478 --> 18:34.046
and they took from each other...

18:34.112 --> 18:36.281
I mean, mainly your people
from mine, but...

18:37.616 --> 18:39.251
...I digress.

18:41.487 --> 18:43.555
But you aren't responsible

18:43.622 --> 18:46.325
for what happened 150 years ago.

18:46.391 --> 18:49.194
Yeah, but I still feel
like I need to do something.

18:49.261 --> 18:52.464
You know, I joined the national
movement for reparations.

18:52.531 --> 18:54.733
I sent five Black people
who I don't even know

18:54.800 --> 18:56.735
money through a Cash App.

18:56.802 --> 18:59.071
Why didn't you send me some?

18:59.137 --> 19:01.039
Well, I tried,
but you blocked me.

19:01.673 --> 19:03.342
Oh, yeah, my bad.

19:04.443 --> 19:06.311
But you see, Dave,

19:06.378 --> 19:07.980
your first instinct

19:08.046 --> 19:10.282
is to try to fix something
that you didn't even do.

19:10.349 --> 19:12.618
You're a good person.

19:12.684 --> 19:14.219
I mean,
you're always there for me

19:14.286 --> 19:17.289
every time I open my door,
whether I want it or not.

19:19.091 --> 19:22.094
You marched with us
when Trey got falsely arrested.

19:22.160 --> 19:24.630
You even ran for office
to help this neighborhood.

19:24.696 --> 19:26.732
Got your ass kicked.

19:27.399 --> 19:29.034
But you ran.

19:29.101 --> 19:32.404
And that's why, to me,
you're more of a second cousin

19:32.471 --> 19:34.740
than a sixth cousin.

19:35.741 --> 19:37.476
Thanks, Calvin.

19:37.543 --> 19:38.977
That means a lot.

19:39.044 --> 19:40.612
Yeah, don't worry about it.

19:41.480 --> 19:42.548
Whoa, whoa.

19:41.480 --> 19:42.548
Oh, okay.

19:42.614 --> 19:44.182
Man, you really
are hurt, huh?

19:44.249 --> 19:46.752
Yeah, that was a
pretty nasty fall.

19:46.818 --> 19:49.421
Look, Dave,
I know that you fell in my yard,

19:49.488 --> 19:53.625
but since we're family now,
you can't sue me.

19:54.126 --> 19:55.527
Sorry, Cousin Dave.

20:01.233 --> 20:04.603
Okay, now, before we all
get lost in our grooves,

20:04.670 --> 20:06.772
uh, I just wanted to
say how honored we are

20:06.838 --> 20:09.508
to be a part
of your family TikTok challenge.

20:09.575 --> 20:11.343
Okay, Dave, enough.
Would you just hit

20:11.410 --> 20:13.345
the damn button.

20:11.410 --> 20:13.345
Okay, all right...

20:13.412 --> 20:16.515
("We Are Family"
by Sister Sledge playing)

20:18.116 --> 20:20.252
Hey! Hey!

20:20.319 --> 20:23.689
(cheering)

20:23.755 --> 20:27.092
♪ We are family ♪

20:27.826 --> 20:31.296
♪ I got all my sisters with me ♪

20:33.565 --> 20:35.634
♪ Everyone can see ♪

20:35.701 --> 20:37.703
♪ We're together ♪

20:37.769 --> 20:40.505
♪ As we walk on by ♪

20:40.572 --> 20:41.506
♪ And ♪

20:41.573 --> 20:42.774
♪ And we fly ♪

20:42.841 --> 20:45.611
♪ Just like birds of a feather ♪

20:45.677 --> 20:47.145
♪ I won't tell... ♪

20:47.212 --> 20:49.314
There ain't no way he's got
some Black in him, baby.

20:49.381 --> 20:52.117
♪ We are family ♪

20:52.184 --> 20:53.385
♪ Yeah, yeah-ee ♪

20:53.452 --> 20:54.953
♪ I got all my sisters
with me. ♪

